1986 /**
1987  * SIP REGISTER state machine
1988  * @private 
1989  * @param {ResponseEvent} responseEvent JAIN SIP response to process
1990  */
1991 PrivateJainSipClientConnector.prototype.processSipRegisterResponse = function(responseEvent) {
1992     console.debug("PrivateJainSipClientConnector:processSipRegisterResponse(): this.sipRegisterState=" + this.sipRegisterState);
1993 
1994     var jainSipResponse = responseEvent.getResponse();
1995     var statusCode = parseInt(jainSipResponse.getStatusCode());
1996     if (this.sipRegisterState === this.SIP_UNREGISTERED_STATE)
1997     {
1998         console.error("PrivateJainSipClientConnector:processSipRegisterResponse(): bad state, SIP response ignored");
1999     }
2000     else if ((this.sipRegisterState === this.SIP_REGISTERING_STATE) || (this.sipRegisterState === this.SIP_REGISTER_REFRESHING_STATE))
2001     {
2002         if (statusCode < 200)
2003         {
2004             console.debug("PrivateJainSipClientConnector:processSipRegisterResponse(): 1XX response ignored");
2005         }
2006         else if(statusCode === 401 || statusCode === 407)
2007         {
2008             if (this.configuration.sipPassword !== undefined && this.configuration.sipLogin !== undefined)
2009             {
2010                 this.sipRegisterState = this.SIP_REGISTERING_401_STATE;
2011                 var jainSipAuthorizationHeader = this.jainSipHeaderFactory.createAuthorizationHeader(jainSipResponse, this.jainSipRegisterRequest, this.configuration.sipPassword, this.configuration.sipLogin);
2012                 // Send authenticated SIP REGISTER request
2013                 this.sendAuthenticatedSipRegisterRequest(jainSipAuthorizationHeader);
2014             }
2015             else
2016             {
2017                 // Authentification required but not SIP credentials in SIP profile
2018                 console.error("PrivateJainSipClientConnector:processSipRegisterResponse(): SIP registration failed:" + jainSipResponse.getStatusCode() + "  " + jainSipResponse.getStatusLine());
2019                 this.reset();
2020                 this.webRTCommClient.onPrivateClientConnectorOpenErrorEvent();
2021             }
2022         }
2023         else if (statusCode === 200)
2024         {
2025             this.sipRegisterState = this.SIP_REGISTERED_STATE;
2026             if (this.openedFlag === false)
2027             {
2028                 this.openedFlag = true;
2029                 this.webRTCommClient.onPrivateClientConnectorOpenedEvent();
2030             }
2031 
2032             if (this.sipUnregisterPendingFlag === true) {
2033                 this.sipUnregisterPendingFlag = false;
2034                 this.sipRegisterState = this.SIP_UNREGISTERING_STATE;
2035                 if (this.sipRegisterRefreshTimer)
2036                 {
2037                     // Cancel SIP REGISTER refresh timer
2038                     clearTimeout(this.sipRegisterRefreshTimer);
2039                 }
2040                 this.sendNewSipRegisterRequest(0);
2041             }
2042             else
2043             {
2044                 // Start SIP REGISTER refresh timeout
2045                 var that = this;
2046                 if (this.sipRegisterRefreshTimer)
2047                     clearTimeout(this.sipRegisterRefreshTimer);
2048                 this.sipRegisterRefreshTimer = setTimeout(function() {
2049                     that.onSipRegisterTimeout();
2050                 }, 40000);
2051             }
2052         }
2053         else
2054         {
2055             console.error("PrivateJainSipClientConnector:processSipRegisterResponse(): SIP registration failed:" + jainSipResponse.getStatusCode() + "  " + jainSipResponse.getStatusLine());
2056             this.reset();
2057             this.webRTCommClient.onPrivateClientConnectorOpenErrorEvent();
2058         }
2059     }
2060     else if (this.sipRegisterState === this.SIP_REGISTERING_401_STATE)
2061     {
2062         if (statusCode < 200)
2063         {
2064             //  No temporary response for SIP REGISTER request 
2065         }
2066         else if (statusCode === 200)
2067         {
2068             this.sipRegisterState = this.SIP_REGISTERED_STATE;
2069             if (this.openedFlag === false)
2070             {
2071                 console.debug("PrivateJainSipClientConnector:processSipRegisterResponse(): this.openedFlag=true");
2072                 this.openedFlag = true;
2073                 this.webRTCommClient.onPrivateClientConnectorOpenedEvent();
2074             }
2075 
2076             if (this.sipUnregisterPendingFlag === true) {
2077                 this.sipUnregisterPendingFlag = false;
2078                 this.sipRegisterState = this.SIP_UNREGISTERING_STATE;
2079                 if (this.sipRegisterRefreshTimer)
2080                 {
2081                     // Cancel SIP REGISTER refresh timer
2082                     clearTimeout(this.sipRegisterRefreshTimer);
2083                 }
2084                 this.sendNewSipRegisterRequest(0);
2085             }
2086             else
2087             {
2088                 // Start SIP REGISTER refresh timeout
2089                 var that = this;
2090                 if (this.sipRegisterRefreshTimer)
2091                     clearTimeout(this.sipRegisterRefreshTimer);
2092                 this.sipRegisterRefreshTimer = setTimeout(function() {
2093                     that.onSipRegisterTimeout();
2094                 }, 40000);
2095             }
2096         }
2097         else
2098         {
2099             console.error("PrivateJainSipClientConnector:processSipRegisterResponse(): SIP registration failed:" + jainSipResponse.getStatusCode() + "  " + jainSipResponse.getStatusLine());
2100             this.reset();
2101             this.webRTCommClient.onPrivateClientConnectorOpenErrorEvent();
2102         }
2103     }
2104     else if (this.sipRegisterState === this.SIP_REGISTERED_STATE)
2105     {
2106         console.error("PrivateJainSipClientConnector:processSipRegisterResponse(): bad state, SIP response ignored");
2107     }
2108     else if (this.sipRegisterState === this.SIP_UNREGISTERING_STATE)
2109     {
2110         if (statusCode < 200)
2111         {
2112             //  Not temporary response for SIP REGISTER request  
2113         }
2114         else if(statusCode === 401 || statusCode === 407)
2115         {
2116             this.sipRegisterState = this.SIP_UNREGISTERING_401_STATE;
2117             jainSipAuthorizationHeader = this.jainSipHeaderFactory.createAuthorizationHeader(jainSipResponse, this.jainSipRegisterRequest, this.configuration.sipPassword, this.configuration.sipLogin);
2118             this.sendAuthenticatedSipRegisterRequest(jainSipAuthorizationHeader);
2119         }
2120         else if (statusCode === 200)
2121         {
2122             this.reset();
2123             this.webRTCommClient.onPrivateClientConnectorClosedEvent();
2124         }
2125         else
2126         {
2127             console.error("PrivateJainSipClientConnector:processSipRegisterResponse(): SIP unregistration failed:" + jainSipResponse.getStatusCode() + "  " + jainSipResponse.getStatusLine());
2128             this.reset();
2129             this.webRTCommClient.onPrivateClientConnectorClosedEvent();
2130         }
2131     }
2132     else if (this.sipRegisterState === this.SIP_UNREGISTERING_401_STATE)
2133     {
2134         if (statusCode < 200)
2135         {
2136             //  Not temporary response for SIP REGISTER request 
2137         }
2138         else if (statusCode === 200)
2139         {
2140             this.reset();
2141             this.webRTCommClient.onPrivateClientConnectorClosedEvent();
2142         }
2143         else
2144         {
2145             console.error("PrivateJainSipClientConnector:processSipRegisterResponse(): SIP unregistration failed:" + jainSipResponse.getStatusCode() + "  " + jainSipResponse.getStatusLine());
2146             this.reset();

2365 WebRTCommCall.prototype.open = function(calleePhoneNumber, configuration) {
2366     console.debug("WebRTCommCall:open():calleePhoneNumber=" + calleePhoneNumber);
2367     console.debug("WebRTCommCall:open():configuration=" + JSON.stringify(configuration));
2368     if (typeof(configuration) === 'object')
2369     {
2370         if (this.webRTCommClient.isOpened())
2371         {
2372             if (this.checkConfiguration(configuration))
2373             {
2374                 if (this.isOpened() === false)
2375                 {
2376                     try
2377                     {
2378                         var that = this;
2379                         this.callerPhoneNumber = this.webRTCommClient.configuration.sip.sipUserName;
2380                         this.calleePhoneNumber = calleePhoneNumber;
2381                         this.configuration = configuration;
2382                         this.connector.open(configuration);
2383 
2384                         // Setup RTCPeerConnection first
2385                         this.createRTCPeerConnection();
2386                         this.peerConnection.addStream(this.configuration.localMediaStream);
2387                         if (this.configuration.messageMediaFlag)
2388                         {
2389                             if (this.peerConnection.createDataChannel)
2390                             {
2391                                 try
2392                                 {
2393                                     this.messageChannel = this.peerConnection.createDataChannel("mymessageChannel", {
2394                                         reliable: false
2395                                     });

2397                                     console.debug("WebRTCommCall:open(): this.messageChannel.reliable=" + this.messageChannel.reliable);
2398                                     console.debug("WebRTCommCall:open(): this.messageChannel.binaryType=" + this.messageChannel.binaryType);
2399                                     this.messageChannel.onopen = function(event) {
2400                                         that.onRtcPeerConnectionMessageChannelOnOpenEvent(event);
2401                                     };
2402                                     this.messageChannel.onclose = function(event) {
2403                                         that.onRtcPeerConnectionMessageChannelOnClose(event);
2404                                     };
2405                                     this.messageChannel.onerror = function(event) {
2406                                         that.onRtcPeerConnectionMessageChannelOnErrorEvent(event);
2407                                     };
2408                                     this.messageChannel.onmessage = function(event) {
2409                                         that.onRtcPeerConnectionMessageChannelOnMessageEvent(event);
2410                                     };
2411                                 }
2412                                 catch (exception)
2413                                 {
2414                                     alert("WebRTCommCall:open():DataChannel not supported");
2415                                 }
2416                             }
2417                         }
2418 
2419                         if (window.webkitRTCPeerConnection)
2420                         {
2421                             var sdpConstraints = {
2422                                 mandatory:
2423                                         {
2424                                             OfferToReceiveAudio: this.configuration.audioMediaFlag,
2425                                             OfferToReceiveVideo: this.configuration.videoMediaFlag
2426                                         },
2427                                 optional: []
2428                             };
2429 
2430                             console.debug("WebRTCommCall:open():sdpConstraints=" + JSON.stringify(sdpConstraints));
2431                             this.peerConnection.createOffer(function(offer) {
2432                                 that.onRtcPeerConnectionCreateOfferSuccessEvent(offer);
2433                             }, function(error) {
2434                                 that.onRtcPeerConnectionCreateOfferErrorEvent(error);
2435                             }, sdpConstraints);
2436                         }
2437                         else if (window.mozRTCPeerConnection)
2438                         {
2439                             var sdpConstraints = {
2440                                     offerToReceiveAudio: this.configuration.audioMediaFlag,
2441                                     offerToReceiveVideo: this.configuration.videoMediaFlag,
2442                                     mozDontOfferDataChannel: !this.configuration.messageMediaFlag
2443                             };
2444 
2445                             console.debug("WebRTCommCall:open():sdpConstraints=" + JSON.stringify(sdpConstraints));
2446                             this.peerConnection.createOffer(function(offer) {
2447                                 that.onRtcPeerConnectionCreateOfferSuccessEvent(offer);
2448                             }, function(error) {
2449                                 that.onRtcPeerConnectionCreateOfferErrorEvent(error);
2450                             }, sdpConstraints);
2451                         }
2452                         console.debug("WebRTCommCall:open():sdpConstraints=" + JSON.stringify(sdpConstraints));
2453                     }
2454                     catch (exception) {
2455                         console.error("WebRTCommCall:open(): catched exception:" + exception);
2456                         setTimeout(function() {
2457                             try {
2458                                 that.eventListener.onWebRTCommCallOpenErrorEvent(that, exception);
2459                             }
2460                             catch (exception)
2461                             {
2462                                 console.error("WebRTCommCall:open(): catched exception in listener:" + exception);
2463                             }
2464                         }, 1);
2465                         // Close properly the communication
2466                         try {
2467 
2468                             this.close();
2469                         } catch (e) {
2470                         }
2471                         throw exception;
2472                     }
2473                 }
2474                 else
2475                 {
2476                     console.error("WebRTCommCall:open(): bad state, unauthorized action");
2477                     throw "WebRTCommCall:open(): bad state, unauthorized action";
2478                 }
2479             }
2480             else
2481             {
2482                 console.error("WebRTCommCall:open(): bad configuration");
2483                 throw "WebRTCommCall:open(): bad configuration";
2484             }
2485         }
2486         else
2487         {
2488             console.error("WebRTCommCall:open(): bad state, unauthorized action");
2489             throw "WebRTCommCall:open(): bad state, unauthorized action";
2490         }
2491     }
2492     else

3712 WebRTCommCall.prototype.setRtcPeerConnectionLocalDescription = function(sdpOffer) {
3713 	var sdpOfferString = sdpOffer.sdp;
3714 	var sdpParser = new SDPParser();
3715 	var parsedSdpOffer = sdpParser.parse(sdpOfferString);
3716 
3717 	// Check if offer is ok with the requested media constraints
3718 	if (window.webkitRTCPeerConnection) {
3719 		if (this.configuration.videoMediaFlag === false)
3720 		{
3721 		    this.removeMediaDescription(parsedSdpOffer, "video");
3722 		}
3723 
3724 		if (this.configuration.audioMediaFlag === false)
3725 		{
3726 		    this.removeMediaDescription(parsedSdpOffer, "audio");
3727 		}
3728 	}
3729 
3730 	if (this.configuration.audioCodecsFilter || this.configuration.videoCodecsFilter || this.configuration.opusFmtpCodecsParameters)
3731 	{
3732 	    try
3733 	    {
3734 		// Apply audio/video codecs filter to RTCPeerConnection SDP offer to
3735 		this.applyConfiguredCodecFilterOnSessionDescription(parsedSdpOffer);
3736 	    }
3737 	    catch (exception)
3738 	    {
3739 		console.error("WebRTCommCall:onRtcPeerConnectionCreateOfferSuccessEvent(): configured codec filtering has failded, use inital RTCPeerConnection SDP offer");
3740 	    }
3741 	}
3742 
3743 	// Check if offer is ok with the requested RTCPeerConnection constraints
3744 	if (this.webRTCommClient.configuration.RTCPeerConnection.forceTurnMediaRelay === true)
3745 	{
3746 	    this.forceTurnMediaRelay(parsedSdpOffer);
3747 	}
3748 	// Allow patching of chrome ice-options for interconnect with Mobicents Media Server, commented for now but to be made configurable
3749 	// this.patchChromeIce(parsedSdpOffer, "ice-options");
3750 	console.debug("WebRTCommCall:onRtcPeerConnectionCreateOfferSuccessEvent(): parsedSdpOffer=" + parsedSdpOffer);
3751 
3752 	// Apply modified SDP Offer
3753 	sdpOffer.sdp = parsedSdpOffer;
3754 	this.peerConnectionLocalDescription = sdpOffer;
3755 
3756 	return parsedSdpOffer;
3757 }

4361  * @private
4362  * @param {SessionDescription} sessionDescription  JAIN (gov.nist.sdp) SDP offer object 
4363  */
4364 WebRTCommCall.prototype.applyConfiguredCodecFilterOnSessionDescription = function(sessionDescription) {
4365     if (sessionDescription instanceof SessionDescription)
4366     {
4367         try
4368         {
4369             console.debug("WebRTCommCall:applyConfiguredCodecFilterOnSessionDescription(): sessionDescription=" + sessionDescription);
4370             // Deep copy the media descriptions
4371             var mediaDescriptions = sessionDescription.getMediaDescriptions(false);
4372             for (var i = 0; i < mediaDescriptions.length; i++)
4373             {
4374                 var mediaDescription = mediaDescriptions[i];
4375                 var mediaField = mediaDescription.getMedia();
4376                 var mediaType = mediaField.getType();
4377                 if (mediaType === "audio")
4378                 {
4379                     if (this.configuration.audioCodecsFilter)
4380                     {
4381                         var offeredAudioCodecs = this.getOfferedCodecsInMediaDescription(mediaDescription);
4382                         // Filter offered codec first
4383                         var splitAudioCodecsFilters = (this.configuration.audioCodecsFilter).split(",");
4384                         this.applyCodecFiltersOnOfferedCodecs(offeredAudioCodecs, splitAudioCodecsFilters);
4385                         // Apply modification on audio media description
4386                         this.updateMediaDescription(mediaDescription, offeredAudioCodecs, splitAudioCodecsFilters);
4387                     }
4388 
4389                     // Add OPUS parameter if required
4390                     if (this.configuration.opusFmtpCodecsParameters)
4391                     {
4392                         this.updateOpusMediaDescription(mediaDescription, this.configuration.opusFmtpCodecsParameters);
4393                     }
4394                 }
4395                 else if (mediaType === "video" && this.configuration.videoCodecsFilter)
4396                 {
4397                     var offeredVideoCodecs = this.getOfferedCodecsInMediaDescription(mediaDescription);
4398                     // Filter offered codec
4399                     var splitVideoCodecFilter = (this.configuration.videoCodecsFilter).split(",");
4400                     this.applyCodecFiltersOnOfferedCodecs(offeredVideoCodecs, splitVideoCodecFilter);
4401                     // Apply modification on video media description
4402                     this.updateMediaDescription(mediaDescription, offeredVideoCodecs, splitVideoCodecFilter);
4403                 }
4404             }
4405         }
4406         catch (exception)
4407         {
4408             console.error("WebRTCommCall:applyConfiguredCodecFilterOnSessionDescription(): catched exception, exception:" + exception);
4409             throw exception;
4410         }
4411     }
4412     else
4413     {
4414         throw "WebRTCommCall:applyConfiguredCodecFilterOnSessionDescription(): bad arguments"
4415     }

4418 /**
4419  * Get offered codecs in media description
4420  * @private
4421  * @param {MediaDescription} mediaDescription  JAIN (gov.nist.sdp) MediaDescription object 
4422  * @return offeredCodec JSON object { "0":"PCMU", "111":"OPUS", .....} 
4423  */
4424 WebRTCommCall.prototype.getOfferedCodecsInMediaDescription = function(mediaDescription) {
4425     console.debug("WebRTCommCall:getOfferedCodecsInMediaDescription()");
4426     if (mediaDescription instanceof MediaDescription)
4427     {
4428         var mediaFormats = mediaDescription.getMedia().getFormats(false);
4429         var foundCodecs = {};
4430 
4431         // Set static payload type and codec name
4432         for (var j = 0; j < mediaFormats.length; j++)
4433         {
4434             var payloadType = mediaFormats[j];
4435             console.debug("WebRTCommCall:getOfferedCodecsInMediaDescription(): payloadType=" + payloadType);
4436             console.debug("WebRTCommCall:getOfferedCodecsInMediaDescription(): this.codecNames[payloadType]=" + this.codecNames[payloadType]);
4437             foundCodecs[payloadType] = this.codecNames[payloadType];
4438         }
4439 
4440         // Set dynamic payload type and codec name 
4441         var attributFields = mediaDescription.getAttributes();
4442         for (var k = 0; k < attributFields.length; k++)
4443         {
4444             var attributField = attributFields[k];
4445             if (attributField.getName() === "rtpmap")
4446             {
4447                 try
4448                 {
4449                     var rtpmapValue = attributField.getValue();
4450                     var splitRtpmapValue = rtpmapValue.split(" ");
4451                     var payloadType = splitRtpmapValue[0];
4452                     var codecInfo = splitRtpmapValue[1];
4453                     var splittedCodecInfo = codecInfo.split("/");
4454                     var codecName = splittedCodecInfo[0];
4455                     foundCodecs[payloadType] = codecName.toUpperCase();
4456                     console.debug("WebRTCommCall:getOfferedCodecsInMediaDescription(): payloadType=" + payloadType);
4457                     console.debug("WebRTCommCall:getOfferedCodecsInMediaDescription(): codecName=" + codecName);
4458                 }
4459                 catch (exception)
4460                 {
4461                     console.error("WebRTCommCall:getOfferedCodecsInMediaDescription(): rtpmap/fmtp format not supported");
4462                 }
4463             }
4464         }
4465         return foundCodecs;
4466     }
4467     else
4468     {
4469         throw "WebRTCommCall:getOfferedCodecsInMediaDescription(): bad arguments"
4470     }
4471 };

4479 WebRTCommCall.prototype.applyCodecFiltersOnOfferedCodecs = function(foundCodecs, codecFilters) {

4511 WebRTCommCall.prototype.updateMediaDescription = function(mediaDescription, filteredCodecs, codecFilters) {
4512     console.debug("WebRTCommCall:updateMediaDescription()");
4513     if (mediaDescription instanceof MediaDescription && typeof(filteredCodecs) === 'object' && codecFilters instanceof Array)
4514     {
4515         // Build new media field format lis
4516         var newFormatListArray = new Array();
4517         for (var i = 0; i < codecFilters.length; i++)
4518         {
4519             for (var offeredCodecPayloadType in filteredCodecs)
4520             {
4521                 if (filteredCodecs[offeredCodecPayloadType] === codecFilters[i]) {
4522                     newFormatListArray.push(offeredCodecPayloadType);
4523                     break;
4524                 }
4525             }
4526         }
4527         mediaDescription.getMedia().setFormats(newFormatListArray);
4528         // Remove obsolte rtpmap attributs

4530         var attributFields = mediaDescription.getAttributes();
4531         for (var k = 0; k < attributFields.length; k++)
4532         {
4533             var attributField = attributFields[k];
4534             if (attributField.getName() === "rtpmap" || attributField.getName() === "fmtp")
4535             {
4536                 try
4537                 {
4538                     var rtpmapValue = attributField.getValue();
4539                     var splitedRtpmapValue = rtpmapValue.split(" ");
4540                     var payloadType = splitedRtpmapValue[0];
4541                     if (filteredCodecs[payloadType] !== undefined)
4542                         newAttributeFieldArray.push(attributField);
4543                 }
4544                 catch (exception)
4545                 {
4546                     console.error("WebRTCommCall:updateMediaDescription(): rtpmap/fmtp format not supported");
4547                 }

4557     }

5108         if (typeof(calleePhoneNumber) === 'string' && typeof(callConfiguration) === 'object')
5109         {
5110             if (this.isOpened())
5111             {
5112                 var newWebRTCommCall = new WebRTCommCall(this);
5113                 newWebRTCommCall.connector = this.connector.createPrivateSessionConnector(newWebRTCommCall);
5114                 newWebRTCommCall.open(calleePhoneNumber, callConfiguration);
5115                 return newWebRTCommCall;
5116             }
5117             else
5118             {
5119                 console.error("WebRTCommClient:call(): bad state, unauthorized action");
5120                 throw "WebRTCommClient:call(): bad state, unauthorized action";
5121             }
5122         }
5123         else
5124         {
5125             console.error("WebRTCommClient:call(): bad argument, check API documentation");
5126             throw "WebRTCommClient:call(): bad argument, check API documentation"
5127         }
5128     }
5129     catch (exception) {
5130         console.error("WebRTCommClient:call(): catched exception:" + exception);
5131         throw exception;
5132     }
5133 };

5233 /**
5234  * Implements PrivateClientConnector closed event listener interface
5235  * @callback PrivatePrivateClientConnector interface
5236  * @private
5237  */
5238 
5239 WebRTCommClient.prototype.onPrivateClientConnectorClosedEvent = function()
5240 {
5241     console.debug("WebRTCommClient:onPrivateClientConnectorClosedEvent()");
5242     var wasOpenedFlag = this.isOpened() || this.closePendingFlag;
5243 
5244     // Close properly the client
5245     try {
5246         if (this.closePendingFlag === false)
5247             this.close();
5248         else
5249             this.connector = undefined;
5250     } catch (exception) {
5251     }
5252 
5253     if (wasOpenedFlag && (this.eventListener.onWebRTCommClientClosedEvent !== undefined))
5254     {
5255         var that = this;
5256         setTimeout(function() {
5257             try {
5258                 that.eventListener.onWebRTCommClientClosedEvent();
5259             }
5260             catch (exception) {
5261                 console.error("WebRTCommClient:onPrivateClientConnectorClosedEvent(): catched exception in event listener:" + exception);
5262             }
5263         }, 1);
5264     }
5265     else if (!wasOpenedFlag && (this.eventListener.onWebRTCommClientOpenErrorEvent !== undefined))
5266     {
5267         var that = this;
5268         setTimeout(function() {
5269             try {
5270                 that.eventListener.onWebRTCommClientOpenErrorEvent("Connection to WebRTCommServer has failed");
5271             }
5272             catch (exception) {
5273                 console.error("WebRTCommClient:onWebRTCommClientOpenErrorEvent(): catched exception in event listener:" + exception);
5274             }
5275         }, 1);
5276     }
5277 };
